</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br><span class="line-number">12</span><br><span class="line-number">13</span><br><span class="line-number">14</span><br><span class="line-number">15</span><br><span class="line-number">16</span><br><span class="line-number">17</span><br><span class="line-number">18</span><br><span class="line-number">19</span><br><span class="line-number">20</span><br><span class="line-number">21</span><br></div></div><h2 id="navbar-toggler" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#navbar-toggler" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Navbar Toggler</h2>
<p>By Default, Navbar toggler is enabled. It shows on smaller screens. If you do not need it, then set <code>toggle-enabled</code>
to <code>false</code>.</p>
<h2 id="navbar-nav" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#navbar-nav" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Navbar Nav</h2>
<p>You can use <code>&lt;NavbarNav&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;Nav&gt;</code> both components. <code>&lt;NavbarNav&gt;</code> is just a wrapper of <code>&lt;Nav&gt;</code> component. Internally,
it adds <code>navs</code> prop to <code>&lt;Nav&gt;</code> component. So, if you are already using <code>&lt;Nav&gt;</code> component in a certain component, just
add <code>navs</code> prop.</p>
<h2 id="color-schemes" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#color-schemes" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Color schemes</h2>
<p>There are two props <code>variant</code> &amp; <code>bg-variant</code>. <code>variant</code> prop is used to make the color lighter or darker. <code>bg-variant</code>
is used to make different background colors.</p>
<h3 id="dark-variants" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#dark-variants" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Dark Variants</h3>
<WNavbar class="mb-2" :bg-variant="variant" variant="dark"
v-for="variant in ['primary' , 'secondary' , 'success' , 'danger' , 'warning', 'info', 'light', 'dark']"
:brand="variant +' Navbar'">
<WNav class="me-auto mb-2 mb-lg-0" navs>
<WNavItem active>Home</WNavItem>
<WNavItem>Link</WNavItem>
<WNavItem disabled>Disabled</WNavItem>
</WNav>
</WNavbar>
<h3 id="light-variants" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#light-variants" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Light Variants</h3>
<WNavbar class="mb-2" :bg-variant="variant" variant="light"
v-for="variant in ['primary' , 'secondary' , 'success' , 'danger' , 'warning', 'info', 'light', 'dark']"
:brand="variant +' Navbar'">
<WNav class="me-auto mb-2 mb-lg-0" navs>
<WNavItem active>Home</WNavItem>
<WNavItem>Link</WNavItem>
<WNavItem disabled>Disabled</WNavItem>
</WNav>
</WNavbar>
<h2 id="position" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#position" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Position</h2>
<p>Use either <code>top</code> or <code>bottom</code> for <code>fixed</code> prop to make a <code>&lt;Navbar&gt;</code> be fixed either at <code>top</code> or <code>bottom</code> respectively.</p>
<div class="language-html ext-html line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-html"><code>
