</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br></div></div><h2 id="scrolling" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#scrolling" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Scrolling</h2>
<p><code>&lt;NavbarNav&gt;</code> can be scrollable when <code>scroll-height</code> prop is set. You can use either <code>numerical</code> value without units,
or <code>string</code> value with units. When <code>numerical</code> value is used, default unit will be <code>px</code>.</p>
<div class="language-html ext-html line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-html"><code>
<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>Navbar</span> <span class="token attr-name">sticky</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation attr-equals">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>bottom<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span> <span class="token attr-name">brand</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation attr-equals">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>Sticky Bottom<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
